#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:789
msgid "Space Amoeba Scenarios"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:791
msgid ""
"Giant Space Amoebas can be added to many of the competitive scenarios in "
"this book. During the game, the Space Amoebas will multiply and attempt "
"to destroy the human players. There are similar rules for Space Amoebas "
"included in the Solo/Co-op Scenario Book (SSB 3.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:799
msgid ""
"• Space Amoebas may be pre-placed in Deep Space between the Home Systems."
" No Deep Space marker is placed in a hex with an Amoeba. • In the "
"diagrams to follow, Space Amoebas are placed on the hexes marked with an "
"“S” as suggestions for the Large 2-Player Map as well as the Standard "
"3-Player and 4-Player Maps. However, players should feel free to play "
"with some other mutually agreed upon layout. • All Space Amoebas are of "
"one type (unless the players agree upon some layout with multiple types)."
" A Space Amoeba counter of any of the three included types may be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:807
msgid ""
"• Unlike the solitary Space Amoeba scenario there are no rule "
"restrictions (i.e., Titans, Ground Combat, Facilities, etc. can be used)."
" • Unlike the solitary Space Amoeba scenario players must pay maintenance"
" as usual. • Unlike the solitary Space Amoeba scenario Barren Planets do "
"have Non-Player Aliens (MRB 18.0) on them. • Like in the solitaire Space "
"Amoeba scenario, Minesweepers (SW) represent Science Vessels (SV), which "
"are needed to defeat the Amoebas. However, Minesweepers pull double duty "
"in the competitive scenario. Minesweeper technology now also counts as "
"Science and must be researched to produce hybrid Minesweeper/Science "
"Vessels. A Minesweeper counter may both research Amoebas and sweep"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:808
msgid ""
"Mines. Use the costs for Minesweeper ships and Minesweeper technology for"
" producing these hybrid ships. • Only the first two levels of Minesweeper"
" technology count as Science technology. Minesweeper 3 technology may be "
"researched and used as normal, but it does not provide any additional "
"bonus to researching Space Amoebas. • If a player is eliminated by an "
"Amoeba, play continues for the remaining players until only one remains "
"(the winner) or until a victory condition is met."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:809
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:812
msgid ""
"Design Note: Yes, I know it says SW on the counters, but in this "
"scenario, it is also as if they say SV, as in Science Vessels. Pretend "
"that the SW was put on the counter by someone who heard the words "
"“Science Vessel” spoken by someone with a bad TV Russian accent (I’m "
"looking at you, Chekov)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:818
msgid "Researching Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:820
msgid ""
"• Until a player has researched the Amoebas, they cannot be attacked and "
"will destroy all that player’s ships (except SVs) in the same hex. If SVs"
" are present, they may research the Amoeba before it destroys the other "
"ships. Once that player’s SVs gather 10 or more Research Points, their "
"other ships will not be automatically destroyed. • Unlike the solitaire "
"scenario, a player is not required to lose a ship to an Amoeba before "
"researching them. • Each player must research the Space Amoebas "
"individually. • Research Points carry over from turn to turn, and each "
"player should track their own research completion. • As soon as an SV is "
"in the same hex with an Amoeba, one or more dice are rolled for each SV "
"to represent that ship’s research into the Amoebas. - 1-2: Two Research "
"Points gained. - 3-5: One Research Point gained. - 6-8: Nothing. - 9-10: "
"SV destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:821
msgid ""
"• Level 1 Science Vessels roll one die when researching. • Level 2 "
"Science Vessels get to roll two dice and use the best result. • Level 2 "
"Science/Minesweeper technology can’t be acquired until a Level 1 Science "
"Vessel has researched an Amoeba (successful or not). • Once a player has "
"a total of 10 Research Points, that player may attack any Amoeba they "
"encounter for the rest of the game. • A Science Vessel may research an "
"Amoeba on the same turn the ship moves into its hex. • Multiple SVs can "
"research each turn they are in a hex with an Amoeba. • If an SV shares a "
"hex with any Amoeba after they are completely researched, that ship still"
" must roll a die for research as normal and may be destroyed on a roll of"
" 9-10. No further Research Points are gained. • After 10 Research Points "
"have been gathered by a player, the Amoebas will no longer automatically "
"destroy their ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:822
msgid ""
"Instead, combat ensues as normal. However, Science Vessels never "
"participate in combat with an Amoeba."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:828
msgid "Space Amoeba Strength"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:830
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:834
msgid ""
"After a player has gathered 10 Research Points, it means they have "
"figured out how to kill the Amoebas. Design Note: In sci-fi terms, the "
"Amoeba can be killed if the player slightly tweaks their weapons – by "
"adjusting the frequency to the upper EM band, by adjusting the phase, by "
"reversing the polarity, or by doing something else pseudo-scientific "
"sounding. The specific adjustment is not important. It means it is now "
"possible to (immediately) attack them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:831
msgid ""
"No retrofit (technology upgrade) is needed for ships in order to attack "
"(MRB 9.11.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:840
msgid "Determine Amoeba Strength"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:842
msgid ""
"• The first player to gather 10 Research Points should roll on the Amoeba"
" Strength Table. This result will apply to all players, but the player "
"who rolled should not reveal the results to other players until they have"
" completed their own research (they may conduct combat vs Amoebas in "
"secrecy). • The results rolled on the Amoeba Strength Table determine the"
" type for all Amoebas in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:848
msgid "Amoeba Strength Table"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:850
msgid "Roll Amoeba Type"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:851
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:862
msgid "C7-1-1"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:852
msgid "D6-2-2"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:853
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:863
msgid "A7-2-2. The Amoebas are also vulnerable to fighters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:854
msgid "A7-2-2. The Amoebas become an A5-1-2 when faced by ONLY Raiders."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:855
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:864
msgid ""
"B5-1-2. The Amoebas have voracious appetites and gets two attacks each "
"round. Each of these attacks may lead to a Chain Attack (10.6.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:856
msgid "6-7"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:857
msgid ""
"A7-2-2. In any round in which there are 3 or more different types of "
"ships (for example: SC, DD, and CA) attacking the Amoebas, all attacking "
"ships get +1 to their attack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:858
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:865
msgid "8-10"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:859
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:866
msgid ""
"The Amoebas can only be killed by detonating a ship inside them. Only one"
" ship may attempt this per turn. If the ship is a CA, BC, BB, DN, or "
"Titan, the Amoeba is destroyed. If the ship is a DD or MB the Amoeba is "
"destroyed on a roll of 1-8 and if the ship is a SC the Amoeba is "
"destroyed on a roll of 1-4. In all cases, the ship attempting this is "
"destroyed. Only the ships listed here can be used. If the Amoeba "
"survives, other ships in the hex with the Amoeba are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:872
msgid "Explanation of Strength Table Results"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:874
msgid ""
"• On a result of 8-10, no adjustment to weapons will work on the Amoebas "
"and the only way to destroy one is by detonating a ship inside of it. • "
"Any other result means it is now possible to attack them and this is the "
"Amoebas’ Attack-Defense-Hull Size in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:880
msgid "Amoeba Properties"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:882
msgid ""
"• All Amoebas have a Tactics Level of 2. • All Amoebas are immune to "
"Cloaking and Fighters unless otherwise specified. • Ships never get a "
"Fleet Size Bonus (MRB 5.1.3) against Amoebas."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:888
msgid "Amoeba Target Priority"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:890
msgid "Each time an Amoeba attacks,"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:891
msgid ""
"these mindless denizens of the interstellar void roll a die to determine "
"which ship they will attempt to swallow (attack). On a roll of 1-5 it "
"will attack the smallest ship in combat. On a roll of 6-10 it will attack"
" the largest ship in the combat. Use the CP value of a ship to determine "
"largest and smallest. Since Flagships are irreplaceable, they are "
"considered to have the highest CP value. If there is a tie, the player "
"chooses the target of the Space Amoeba. If a player chooses to, they may "
"allow their SVs to be attacked (sometimes useful after the Amoebas have "
"been researched as the SVs have a chance to be destroyed anyway."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:897
msgid "Amoeba Attack Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:899
msgid "The Amoeba rolls one die"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:900
msgid ""
"and executes the attack normally, comparing its Attack Strength to the "
"ship’s Defense Strength (including technology). However, larger ships are"
" even harder to swallow. Ships with a Hull Size of 2 get an extra +1 to "
"their Defense Strength and ships with a Hull Size of 3 (or larger) get an"
" extra +2 to their Defense Strength. A successful attack results in the "
"ship being swallowed (destroyed) regardless of size. As always, a roll of"
" 1 is a successful attack and will swallow a ship, regardless of Defense "
"Strength and size."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:906
msgid "Chain Attacks"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:908
msgid "If an Amoeba successfully swallows a ship,"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:909
msgid ""
"and rolls 2 or less than was needed, then the extra energy gained from "
"swallowing the ship allows the Amoeba to immediately attack again. This "
"can happen any number of times during a round of combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:910
msgid ""
"EXAMPLE: A Type 4 Amoeba (A7-2-2) is being attacked by four Scouts, a "
"Cruiser, and a Battleship. All of the ships have Defense Technology 1. "
"The Amoeba attacks first. It rolls a 3 and so will attack the smallest "
"ship (a Scout). On its attack, it rolls a 4. Since it needed a 6, the "
"Amoeba not only swallows the Scout but gets to attack again. This time it"
" rolls a 6 and will attack the largest ship (the Battleship). The "
"Battleship has a Defense Strength of 5 (Defense of 2 + Defense Tech 1 + 2"
" because of Hull Size 3). The Amoeba rolls a 1, swallowing the "
"Battleship. However, since it was only one less than was needed, it does "
"not get to make a further chain attack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:916
msgid "Amoeba Healing"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:918
msgid "After combat, damage to an Amoeba"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:919
msgid "is healed in the same way as ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:925
msgid "Spreading Of Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:927
msgid ""
"Amoebas never move. Once placed, an Amoeba counter never moves to a new "
"hex. Instead, Amoebas spread at the start of the Economic Phase before "
"players make any purchases."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:933
msgid "Spread Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:935
msgid "Amoeba spreading is not random."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:936
msgid ""
"The following guidelines and restrictions apply to the spreading: • Space"
" Amoebas do not start spreading until Economic Phase 7 (or a different "
"phase upon the mutual agreement of all players). • Only one Amoeba may "
"ever be in a hex. • Each Amoeba may only spread one time into one hex "
"during an Economic Phase. • In turn order, each player picks an Amoeba "
"and chooses the hex that it will spread to, placing a new Amoeba in that "
"hex. This process continues until all Amoebas have spread once. • If an "
"Amoeba can spread onto a planet, when selected for spreading, it must "
"spread to the planet hex. If it can spread to multiple planets, the "
"person selecting it can choose which planet hex it spreads to. The "
"presence or absence of a Colony is not a factor. • Newly placed Amoebas "
"do not spread. New Amoebas placed that Economic Phase should be marked in"
" some way so that they are not accidentally selected to spread. • Because"
" Amoebas are attracted to the energy signature of the players’ Empires, "
"they will never spread outside of the map area denoted by the chosen "
"scenario map. • Space Amoebas will not spread into the same hex as a "
"Doomsday Machine and a DM will not move into or through a hex with an "
"Amoeba. • Amoebas are not limited by the number of counters available. "
"Use substitutions when necessary."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:942
msgid "Amoeba Contact with Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:944
msgid "If there are ships in the"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:945
msgid ""
"hex in which an Amoeba spreads, a special combat round occurs immediately"
" during the Economic Phase, with the Amoeba as the attacker. If a player "
"with ships in that hex has not gathered 10 Research Points, all their "
"ships that are not Science Vessels are destroyed (SVs get a Research "
"roll). Space Amoebas automatically destroy neutral Non-Player Alien ships"
" when they spread into their hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:951
msgid "Amoeba Contact with System Markers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:953
msgid "An Amoeba"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:954
msgid ""
"removes the System marker or Terrain Tile (MRB 6.10, whether explored or "
"not) in any hex in which it spreads (only after defeating any ships "
"present). If a hex has not been explored, the Amoeba spreads normally and"
" the System marker is removed, sight unseen."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:955
msgid ""
"An Amoeba will not spread into Black Holes (MRB 6.3) or Supernovas (MRB "
"6.5). Amoebas skip hexes with Folds In Space (MRB 25.2) as normal, but in"
" all other cases, Amoebae are totally unaffected by System markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:961
msgid "Space Amoebas And Mines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:963
msgid ""
"Space Amoebas are hindered from spreading by Mines. However, Mines never "
"affect Amoebas like they do ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:969
msgid "Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:971
msgid "If a player moves only a Mine (or a Mine"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:972
msgid ""
"and Science Vessels) into the same hex as an Amoeba, no combat occurs. In"
" the Economic Phase, the Mine is removed, and that Amoeba does not spread"
" during that one Economic Phase. No other harm comes to the Amoeba."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:978
msgid "Contact with Mines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:980
msgid "Amoebas may spread onto Mines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:981
msgid ""
"normally; in which case the Mines have no effect but will remain in the "
"hex until the next Economic Phase when they may stop the Amoeba from "
"spreading as noted above. A Mine only stops an Amoeba from spreading if "
"it is in the same hex as the Amoeba at the start of the Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:987
msgid "Adapting to Mines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:989
msgid "Amoebas will eventually"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:990
msgid ""
"adapt to the use of Mines. Once each Economic Phase an Amoeba does not "
"spread because of any player’s Mine, roll a die. On a result of 9-10, "
"Amoebas will no longer be prevented from spreading by Mines in future "
"Economic Phases. At the conclusion of every Economic Phase, a Mine will "
"be immediately destroyed when occupying a hex with an Amoeba. Place a “No"
" Mine” counter on one of the Amoebas as a reminder that Mines no longer "
"affect them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:996
msgid "2-Player Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1003
msgid "3-Player Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1010
msgid "4-Player Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1017
msgid "Alternate Victory Scenarios"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1019
msgid ""
"Both of the following alternate victory scenarios can be played in "
"conjunction with almost every scenario in the game. A player still wins "
"by being the first to destroy a Homeworld, but there is also another way "
"to win through Victory Points (VPs). You can’t focus so much on the other"
" way to win that you let your defense go slack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1020
msgid ""
"Use victory point chips or money from another game or scrap paper to "
"track VPs. Everyone’s total score is always known and is open "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1026
msgid "King Of The Warp Point"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1028
msgid ""
"The Warp Points are the key to victory in this scenario. They represent "
"access to vast scientific treasures and ancient civilizations. By "
"studying them, players unlock knowledge that will lead them to make "
"galaxy changing advances."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1036
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1042
msgid "Before the Deep Space markers are placed on"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1037
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1043
msgid ""
"the map, the Warp Points (MRB 28.2) are taken out of the mix. Depending "
"on the scenario, a number of Warp Points are placed in mutually agreed "
"upon hexes in the Deep Space portion of the map. Some guidelines on Warp "
"Point placement: • It is strongly suggested that you use either: - One "
"Warp Point, or - One less Warp Point than the number of players, or - One"
" more Warp Point than the number of players. • All of the Warp Points can"
" be placed centrally, or one could be placed to the advantage of each "
"player with an extra one in the middle. There are a lot of options, and "
"each will change the game. Design Note: Each of the above will make for a"
" very different and interesting game – is it important to hold one Warp "
"Point or do I need to hold several?"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1038
msgid ""
"If the players cannot agree on the placement of the Warp Points, one "
"player should place all the Warp Points while the other players choose "
"their starting positions once the Warp Points have been placed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1039
msgid ""
"Unused Warp Points should be placed to the side and not mixed in with the"
" rest of the Deep Space Markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1049
msgid "Warp Point Properties"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1051
msgid "None of the Warp Points in this"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1052
msgid "scenario are connected. Their only purpose is to provide VPs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1058
msgid "Minesweepers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1060
msgid "These ships have a dual function in this"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1061
msgid ""
"scenario. They not only sweep Mines, but also act as Science Vessels. You"
" must still research Minesweeping Technology to build SWs (MRB 17.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1067
msgid "Game Length"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1069
msgid "Players should decide at the start of the"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1070
msgid ""
"game how many Economic Phases they want the game to last. The game ends "
"after that Economic Phase. 10-12 Econ Phases are good for a shorter game,"
" depending on the scenario. This scenario also works with a longer game "
"of 15-20 Econ Phases, although players in that one will have to be "
"careful not to become too focused on the Warp Points as it will become "
"more and more likely that someone will launch a game-winning attack "
"against a Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1076
msgid "Victory Points"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1078
msgid "Players score 1 VP during the Economic"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1079
msgid ""
"Phase for each Warp Point that shares a hex with one or more of their "
"Science Vessels. All Science Vessels in the same hex as a Warp Point must"
" be revealed during the Economic Phase. The player with the most VPs at "
"the end of the agreed upon number of Economic Phases is the winner. In "
"the event of a tie, after the purchases for the Economic Phase are "
"completed, the players add up the CP value of all combat-capable ships "
"they have on the board and the winner is the player whose fleet adds up "
"to the most CP. In the event of another tie, the tied players share the "
"win."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1085
msgid "Alternate Point Scoring"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1087
msgid "As a twist to this scenario,"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1088
msgid ""
"players can agree that they will score 1 VP per Science Vessel at a Warp "
"Point in the Economic Phase. This will change the scenario strategy "
"significantly (weighing combat capability versus number of Science "
"Vessels is tough) and it is recommended that this version is played with "
"only one Warp Point."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1094
msgid "Grab The Artifacts"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1096
msgid ""
"Ancient artifacts of great value litter Deep Space and players must "
"gather and study them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1104
msgid "Extra pieces or counters will be needed for this"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1105
msgid ""
"scenario (pieces from an old Risk game will work well). One of these "
"extra pieces is placed in every Deep Space hex (along with the "
"exploration marker). These will represent the ancient artifacts."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1111
msgid "Exploring Artifacts"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1113
msgid "After exploration, artifacts remain"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1114
msgid ""
"in the hex even if the System marker is removed (Danger!, etc.). "
"Exception: Artifacts in Supernovas (MRB 6.5), Folds In Space (MRB 25.2), "
"and Quantum Filaments (MRB 25.5) are removed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1120
msgid "Moving Artifacts"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1122
msgid "Artifacts may only be moved by"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1123
msgid ""
"Miners. Place the artifact on the Miner counter when a Miner picks it up."
" They may pick up an artifact at any point during their move. The "
"following rules apply to moving artifacts:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1124
msgid ""
"• Each Miner may carry only one artifact at a time and may not carry "
"minerals or Space Wrecks at the same time. • Artifacts being towed by "
"Miners are destroyed if the Miner is destroyed. • Miners may drop off "
"artifacts at their Homeworld or at a Colony that is connected by MS "
"Pipelines to the Homeworld (it is assumed a civilian ship is able to "
"transport the artifact from there). Miners may not drop off artifacts at "
"Colonies that are not yet connected in this way."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1132
msgid "Each artifact dropped off is worth"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1133
msgid ""
"1 VP the instant it is dropped off. The game ends immediately (even in "
"the middle of a turn) once someone has scored enough VPs that there is no"
" possible way that their total may be passed by another player given the "
"artifacts remaining on the board. In the event of a tie, the person who "
"achieved their Victory Point total first is declared the winner."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1139
msgid "Taking A Stand"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1141
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1145
msgid "(2-Player Variant)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1142
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1146
msgid ""
"The following variants add the use of plastic stands which either provide"
" more access to information or add an additional element of hidden "
"information to the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1152
msgid "Standing Ships Variant"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1154
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1157
msgid ""
"• Unrevealed ships are not placed face down as in the normal game. "
"Instead, ships are placed upright in stands facing the player. • The "
"number of ships in each group is tracked on the Ship Technology Sheet. • "
"When a group is revealed, it is placed face up and a numeral marker "
"placed underneath. • Groups still have a limit of six ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1163
msgid "2-Player Hidden Exploration"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1165
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1168
msgid "VARIANT"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1174
msgid "Changes to Exploration"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1176
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1179
msgid ""
"• The map is set up normally, with face down System markers. • Deep Space"
" markers must be explored by both sides. When a Deep Space System marker "
"is explored or would be returned face up with Exploration technology (MRB"
" 9.8) for the first time, it is not flipped face up and it may not be "
"left face down. Instead, it is placed upright in a stand facing the "
"exploring player. Some markers will be facing one player and some the "
"other, depending on who explored it. If a marker is explored by the other"
" player, it is then removed from the stand and placed face up. All "
"markers that have been explored by both players will be face up on the "
"board. • When a Deep Space System marker is explored by a ship for the "
"first time, a Decoy (MRB 8.3) may be added to the hex. Players may "
"scuttle another decoy during the exploration phase to accommodate this. "
"After looking at the System marker and placing it in a stand, the player "
"removes either the Decoy or the exploring ship. There will be one marker "
"left in the hex, but the other player will not know whether it is a Decoy"
" or a ship and therefore will be less likely to know if the Exploration "
"went well. - If the System marker indicates that the hex is safe, the "
"player removes the Decoy. - If the System marker indicates the ship’s "
"destruction, the player removes the ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1187
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1191
#, python-format
msgid ""
"• Deep Space Black Holes (MRB 6.3) are 100% deadly until explored by both"
" players. If not face up or in a stand, a Deep Space Black Hole will "
"always suck in the first exploring ship(s) (no need to roll the die). "
"When this occurs, the Decoy marker is left behind. Future ships entering "
"the hex roll the die as normal (which will give"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1188
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1192
#, python-format
msgid ""
"away that this is a Black Hole) • Alien planets (MRB 18.0) are also 100% "
"deadly if attacked by a lone ship. The first time an alien planet is "
"discovered and placed in a stand, it is treated like a Danger! marker and"
" the exploring ship is removed without die rolls (leaving the Decoy "
"marker behind). NPA ships are not chosen and placed in the hex until both"
" sides have explored the planet or it is attacked by more than one ship. "
"• Lost in Space markers (MRB 6.6) are treated like Danger! markers when "
"first explored. Future ships from the same player entering the hex later "
"ignore the effect. • Space Pirates (MRB 25.7) are turned face up and "
"handled normally. • Regional Maps (MRB 25.6) are turned face up and "
"handled normally (which could cause adjacent markers to be put in "
"stands). • Minerals (MRB 6.7) and Space Wrecks (MRB 6.8) are placed in "
"stands. However, if that player sends a Miner into the hex, it can be "
"removed from the stand and picked up normally. • Supernovas (MRB 6.5) are"
" treated like Danger! markers (MRB 6.4) when first explored. If explored "
"by a ship, the Decoy is left behind in the hex and must be moved out "
"during the next turn. It is possible that this could cause a Decoy to "
"pass through a Supernova and out the other side under this one exception."
" The player that has explored the Supernova may not send ships into the "
"hex. • Folds In Space (MRB 25.2) have no effect when first explored, "
"remove the Decoy. Future ships may either enter the hex and ignore the "
"usual effects or move through it. Once a ship moves through it remove the"
" marker from the stand and place it face up. • Quantum Filaments (MRB "
"25.5) are treated like Danger! markers when first explored. Future ships "
"from the same player may enter, but must spend an extra movement hex as "
"normal. • Note that a player may ignore beneficial terrain effects (e.g. "
"Pulsars MRB 25.4) to keep the terrain tile hidden from their opponent."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1198
msgid "Game Effects"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1200
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1368
msgid ""
"• This variant creates paths that can be easily traversed by one player "
"(because they’ve explored it), but not the other. That will at times "
"allow a fleet to more easily retreat or avoid combat. • Both players are "
"more likely to research Exploration technology because they will not be "
"able to easily use a path made by the other player. • The cost of "
"suffering a bad exploration result is slightly less because the player "
"will receive a Decoy as a result. • There will be more Decoys on the "
"board."
msgstr ""

