#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1255
msgid "Expanded Sequence of Play"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1256
#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1423
msgid ""
"This is NOT meant to be used in normal game play. This is meant to "
"resolve any disputes or confusion integrating all rules from the base "
"game and all three expan­sions. It is meant to be a final arbiter on any "
"possible confusion. Honestly, you will probably never need this, but it "
"is here if you do. 1. Determine Player Order (first turn of the game "
"only) 2. Turn One: Player 1: a. Movement. b. Combat. c. Exploration. Note"
" that if Exploration results in hostile forces in the same hex return to "
"Step b. immediately and resolve the combat now. Player(s) 2-8: Same as "
"Player 1. After all players have had a turn any Doomsday Machines on the "
"map move. 3. Turn Two: Same as turn one. 4. Turn Three: Same as turn one."
" 5. Economic Phase – All players conduct this phase simultaneously, not "
"in player order. Exception to that is Resource Cards, which are played at"
" the Start of the Economic Phase in Reverse Player Order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1257
msgid ""
"• The attacker states that they have Raiders and want to continue moving."
" • The defender states that they have Scanner 1 (and the attacker must "
"stop) or that they lack Scanner 1 (and the attacker may continue moving)."
" • If the defender stated that they had Scanner 1 the attacker may "
"declare Cloaking 2. • The defender states that they have Scanner 2 (and "
"that the attacker must stop) or that they lack Scanner 2 (and the "
"attacker may continue moving)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1258
msgid ""
"The defender has the option of not announcing their Scanner level and "
"allowing the Raiders to continue to move. Tech levels must be announced "
"in combat (See Step C8), but combat has not been declared at this point."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1259
msgid ""
"Black Hole Survival Checks: These happen before Reaction Movement is "
"declared and before non-combat ships are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1260
msgid ""
"A ship with Advanced Comm Array cannot React into a black hole hex if the"
" enemy ship is attempting a Black Hole Slingshot. That ship can still "
"React to the next hex the enemy ship enters, if that hex is adjacent to "
"the ship making the Reaction Movement."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1261
msgid "MOVEMENT"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1262
msgid ""
"If the attacker uses the Black Hole Slingshot rule to move to another hex"
" any non-combat ships are destroyed before the attacking ships leave."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1263
msgid ""
"Units may move from one hex to another at up to the maximum speed they "
"are equipped with. This movement may be increased by MS Pipelines or "
"Black Hole Slingshots, but not both. This movement may be reduced by "
"entering various terrain types, hexes that contain enemy units, and hexes"
" that are beside enemy units equipped with Advanced Comm Array. Ships use"
" Exploration technology before moving. One or more Resource Cards may be "
"played after Exploration tech is used but before any ship movement."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1264
msgid "NON-COMBAT SHIPS SPECIAL MOVEMENT RULES"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1265
msgid ""
"Units without an Attack Strength may not enter hexes that contain enemy "
"units, enemy Colonies, or face-down System markers unless a friendly "
"combat- capable ship also enters the hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1266
msgid ""
"Units without an Attack Strength are destroyed if caught alone in a hex "
"by combat-capable enemy units. No information about the enemy units is "
"revealed by this except for the fact that they are armed. There are two "
"exceptions to this rule: • Units without an Attack Strength are not "
"destroyed if they are in a Black Hole hex and all of the enemy units fail"
" their Black Hole survival checks."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1267
msgid ""
"Raiders vs. Scanners: When the attacker moves into a hex with enemy units"
" and the attacker has Raiders present that they wish to continue moving, "
"the following happens. (Note that though these rules refer to Raiders, "
"they also cover any other ships equipped with Cloaking.)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1268
msgid ""
"• Units without an Attack Strength and not in a Black Hole hex are not "
"destroyed if friendly combat-capable units declare that they will use "
"Advanced Comm Array to React into the hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1269
msgid "COMBAT"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1270
msgid ""
"C1 Combat-capable units or Colonies from two opposing sides are in the "
"same hex after a player has finished moving."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1271
msgid ""
"C2 Defender may move ships by Reaction Movement if they have the "
"technology needed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1272
msgid "C3 • Attacker declares whether they have Cloaking 1 or not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1273
msgid ""
"• Defender declares whether they have Scanner 1 or not. • If defender has"
" Scanner 1, attacker declares if they have Cloaking 2 or not. • If "
"attacker declared they have Cloaking 2, then defender declares if they "
"have Scanner 2 or not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1274
msgid ""
"C4 • Defender declares whether they have Cloaking 1 or not. • Attacker "
"declares that they have Scanner 1 or not. • If attacker has Scanner 1, "
"defender declares if they have Cloaking 2 or not. • If defender declared "
"they have Cloaking 2 then attacker declares if they have Scanner 2 or "
"not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1275
msgid ""
"C5 Play Resource cards that are played before ships are revealed (Missed "
"Rendezvous, Retreat When Engaged, and Alien Reinforcements)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1276
msgid ""
"Raiders and Missed Rendezvous: If Missed Rendezvous causes a situation in"
" which there are no ships equipped with Scanner until Round 2, there are "
"three possibilities: 1. If the Raider side has nothing but Raiders and "
"they are trying to avoid combat by staying cloaked after learning this, "
"then the battle does"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1277
msgid ""
"not start until the Scanner-equipped ship arrives and Round 2 will count "
