#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1348
msgid "Comprehensive Example of Combat"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1349
msgid ""
"In this example, a Yellow fleet of 15 combat-capable ships and one non-"
"combat ship enters a hex with a Green fleet and Colony. All units have "
"been revealed and Decoys have been removed. The number of each ship is "
"indicated by the number below the group markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1350
msgid ""
"Detonate Mines: Yellow has not brought along any Minesweepers so the Mine"
" in the Green fleet detonates. The Green player selects a CV as the "
"Mine’s target. Since there is now only 1 CV left, 3 of the Fighters are "
"also destroyed. This is a huge loss for the Yellow fleet. The Green Mine "
"is removed from play."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1351
msgid ""
"Combat Screening: Next, players form their battle lines. Yellow has 11 "
"combat-capable ships remaining versus 9 Green combat-capable ships – "
"Yellow may therefore screen two of their own ships. The Colony Ship is a "
"non-combat ship and is automatically screened until the end of the battle"
" and doesn’t count against this limit. Their CV cannot be targeted until "
"all their Fighters are destroyed, so Yellow doesn’t screen any ships. "
"Note that Green’s Colony cannot be attacked until all of Green’s ships "
"have been destroyed or retreated."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1352
msgid ""
"Fleet Size Bonus: Neither side has twice as many ships as the other, so "
"neither player receives this +1 bonus."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1353
msgid ""
"Technologies: Both players have the same Tactics Level, so ties in Weapon"
" Class ratings will be decided in the defender’s favor. Both players have"
" Fighter Technology 1, which means their Fighters are B-Class, Attack 5, "
"and Defense 0. Neither player has invested in Attack or Defense "
"Technologies, so Attack and Defense Strengths will be unmodified. Both "
"players have Level 1 Cloaking. Neither has Scanner Technology to negate "
"Cloaking but the Yellow Raiders still opt to participate in the combat. "
"Neither player has Point Defense."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1354
msgid ""
"Green Fires A-Class: First to fire will be the defender’s A-Class rated "
"ships, but they have only one – their Base. Green fires their Base "
"(Attack 7) against one of the Raiders (Defense 0). The Base will hit the "
"Raider on a roll of 1-7. A 5 is rolled, so the Raider group receives a "
"Hit marker. Since it takes two hits to eliminate each Raider, the Hit "
"marker has no effect until a second hit is applied against the Raider "
"group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1355
msgid ""
"Yellow Fires A-Class: Now it’s Yellow’s turn to fire their A-Class rated "
"ships. Since Green does not have Scanner Technology, the 2 Yellow Raiders"
" are considered Cloaked and therefore have an A-Class rating. Cloaking 1 "
"gives them an Attack Strength of 4. During this first round of combat "
"(only), they get a +1 to their Attack Strength. Both fire on the "
"Battlecruiser group, needing a 1-4 to hit (5-1=4). The die rolls are 10 "
"and 8 – both misses. Next the 2 BBs also fire on the Battlecruiser group."
" The BBs similarly need a 1-4 to hit. The rolls are 7 and 2; one hit is "
"achieved. A Hit marker is placed on the Green BC group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1356
msgid ""
"The rest of the attacks for round #1 are summarized below. The "
"parenthetical numbers are the ship’s Attack or Defense Strength, as "
"appropriate."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1357
msgid ""
"Green B-Class: 2 Fighters (5) and 2 BCs (5) fire on the 3 remaining "
"Yellow Fighters (0). 1-5 needed. 2 are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1358
msgid ""
"Yellow B-Class: The Fighter (5) fires on the Shipyard (0). 1-5 needed to "
"hit. One hit destroys it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1359
msgid ""
"Green C-Class: 2 CAs (4) fire on the Yellow CA group (1). 1-3 needed to "
"hit. One hit is achieved."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1360
msgid ""
"Yellow C-Class: 2 CAs (4) fire on the Green BCs (1). 1-3 needed to hit. "
"Two more hits are achieved. Since there are now three hits on this group,"
" one BC is eliminated, and the remaining BC has one hit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1361
msgid ""
"Green E-Class: The Scout (3) fires on the Yellow Fighter (0). 1-3 needed "
"to hit. A hit destroys the last Yellow Fighter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1362
msgid ""
"Yellow E-Class: The CV (3) fires on one of the Green Fighters (0). 1-3 "
"needed to hit. One hit destroys it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1363
msgid ""
"The surviving ships are shown below. Since Yellow still has the majority "
"of combat-capable ships (8 to 6), they elect to screen their CV since it "
"is now vulnerable without the Fighters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1364
msgid ""
"In the second round of combat, ships may now retreat instead of firing – "
"retreating takes place at the moment the ship can fire."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1365
msgid ""
"First up to fire is the Green Base and fire proceeds in the same order as"
" the first round. The battle proceeds for as many rounds as it takes "
"until one player is destroyed or all their units retreat. In this "
"example, Yellow may have a slight advantage, but the battle is bound to "
"be bloody for each side."
msgstr ""
